### Purpose

A launcher for pre-made Claude Code agents running in isolated Docker containers. Each agent has distinct instructions, model, and parameters, but they share OAuth credentials, workspace, and slash commands. Eliminates the friction of re-authenticating and re-configuring Claude Code per persona.

### Tech Stack

- Python 3 (single-file launcher, ~100 lines, no packaging)
- Docker + Docker Compose (one container per launched agent)
- Debian Bookworm slim base image; Claude Code CLI installed via `claude.ai/install.sh`
- Python deps: `pick` (TUI picker), `python-dotenv` (parse `.conf` files)
- `ripgrep` installed via apt; container forces system `rg` via `USE_BUILTIN_RIPGREP=0`
- No tests, no CI, no lockfile

